      "content": "But what is there to hold onto? A hollow shell cannot be mended. To exist in this state, merely performing the motions of a living soul while feeling nothing but the cold ache of betrayal... it feels less like living and more like a punishment. Is it not more dignified to accept the inevitable than to linger in such a wretched, half-broken state?",
